                        "content": "A nurse is educating prospective foster families on health care considerations for the foster child. Which statement made by a family member indicates a need for further teaching?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nA foster child can often have complex health conditions. Frequent health visits will be needed during the transition from foster care to home to ensure that the child is acclimated well without any health concerns arising. Therefore option 3 is an incorrect statement by the family member, indicating the need for further teaching. Options 1, 2, and 4 are accurate statements.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, need for further teaching. These words indicate a negative event query and the need to select the incorrect statement by the family member. Thinking about the complexity of the care of a foster child will direct you to option 3. Community resources, a social worker, and a multidisciplinary team are necessary components to caring for a foster child. Also, note the closed-ended word \"all\" in this option.",
